He s lived and worked in 222 countries and has been a force within of some of the biggest multinationals like Sandoz (known as Novartis today), Otis, SAA, and Sanlam. Nevertheless, Bonang Mohale, Shell South Africa s Vice President Upstream &amp; Chairman Downstream was &#8211; in his own words &#8211; a typical township boy .So what is it that took him to the dizzying heights and hallowed halls that he occupies today? What wisdom is it that both private business and government seek, from the man who started life as a young boy who had absolutely no doubt of his ability to achieve whatever he set his mind to? In this 2 minute Quick Insight video, extracted from a full length interview, Mohale shares some of the aspects of his particular brand of leadership.Watch the full length video here.In partnership with FNB, Moneyweb presents this bespoke leadership video series with top business people. The interview draws on the person s life, failures and the lessons they have learnt on their journey to the successful leadership positions they hold today.Other business leaders share their stories here.